This is a [vital.vim](https://github.com/vim-jp/vital.vim) module to echo string preserving colored output by ANSI color sequence.

```vim
let s:V = vital#of('vital')
let s:C = s:V.import('ColorEcho')

call s:C.echo(system('git diff --color'))
```

Here is a screenshot of example where showing `crystal` command's colorful output in Vim by [vim-crystal](https://github.com/rhysd/vim-crystal).

![screen shot: run spec](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rhysd/ss/master/vim-crystal/spec.gif)

